<image 1>Which graph above best shows the maximum kinetic energy K of the photoelectrons as a function of the frequency of incident light?

A. A
B. B
C. C
D. D

The maximum kinetic energy of photoelectrons is inversely proportional to the frequency of the incident light. This is because the maximum kinetic energy is the energy required to overcome the work function of the metal, which is inversely proportional to the frequency of the incident light. Therefore, the correct graph is D.
